PN,31101
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,FThe former chief economist of the Bank
OL,8,Fof England says it is "relatively
OL,9,Funlikely" that interest rates will
OL,10,Frise in response to the surge in
OL,11,Fenergy prices triggered by the war in
OL,12,FIran.
OL,14,FThe spike in gas and oil prices is
OL,15,Fcreating a fresh wave of inflation,
OL,16,Fand financial markets are currently
OL,17,Fbetting on at least two rate increases
OL,18,Fbefore the end of the year.
OL,26,@pD@WOUqD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,F"There will be a pick-up in inflation,
OL,8,Fbut it will be a manageable one. Big
OL,9,Ffigure? Three and a bit (per cent),"
OL,10,Fsaid Andy Haldane, now president of
OL,11,Fthe British Chambers of Commerce.
OL,13,FHaldane said the upward pressure on
OL,14,Fprices caused by the war in the Gulf
OL,15,Fis "not remotely" on the scale of that
OL,16,Ftriggered by Russia's invasion of
OL,17,FUkraine.
OL,19,FAndy Haldane tells ITV News he thinks
OL,20,Finterest rate hikes at this stage are
OL,21,F"unlikely"
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@YpmqD@bpnqD@dO]wD@DOUwD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,F"There's no immediate cause for the
OL,8,FBank of England to be slamming on the
OL,9,Fbrakes with higher interest rates," he
OL,10,Ftold ITV News.
OL,12,F"I think were energy prices to take a
OL,13,Ffurther leg north, which is not out of
OL,14,Fthe question, that would be a game
OL,15,Fchanger for the likely path of
OL,16,Finterest rates. But for now, growth in
OL,17,Fthe economy calls for lower interest
OL,18,Frates, not higher ones."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,FThe Organisation for Economic Co-
OL,8,Foperation and Development (OECD)
OL,9,Fbelieves the UK faces the biggest hit
OL,10,Fto growth from the war among the G20
OL,11,Fadvanced economies.
OL,13,FIt now forecasts the UK economy will
OL,14,Fexpand by just 0.7% in 2026 - down
OL,15,Ffrom a previous projection of 1.2% -
OL,16,Fthe largest downgrade in its updated
OL,17,Foutlook, released this morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,FThe OECD also expects the headline
OL,8,Frate of inflation in the UK to rise to
OL,9,F4% this year, the second-highest in
OL,10,Fthe G7 after the United States -
OL,11,Fhighlighting how exposed the UK is to
OL,12,Frising energy prices.
OL,14,FThe UK remains very dependent on
OL,15,Fimported energy and pays some of the
OL,16,Fhighest prices in the developed world
OL,17,Fto consume it.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,FWe rely more heavily on natural gas
OL,8,Ffor heating and electricity generation
OL,9,Fthan many other countries, and have
OL,10,Frelatively little storage capacity as
OL,11,Fa buffer against sudden price shocks.
OL,13,FHaldane argues the UK's energy
OL,14,Fvulnerability needs to be addressed.
OL,16,F"Unless and until that happens, the UK
OL,17,Fwill remain... caught in the
OL,18,Fcrosshairs of geopolitical risk," he
OL,19,Fwarned.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,FDrilling in the North Sea wouldn't
OL,8,Fcurb the cost of living, Andy Haldane
OL,9,Ftold ITV News
OL,11,FIn Haldane's view, increasing drilling
OL,12,Fin the North Sea would do little to
OL,13,Fcushion the UK from higher energy
OL,14,Fprices, but he thinks the government
OL,15,Fshould keep the option of opening new
OL,16,Ffields on the table.
OL,18,F"It wouldn't curb the cost of living,
OL,19,Fbut it would top up the coffers - the
OL,20,Ftax revenues of government," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,FHaldane described the war in the
OL,8,FMiddle East as a "seismic shock" for
OL,9,Fboth British businesses and households.
OL,11,FConsumer confidence is fragile.
OL,12,FCompanies are being squeezed by a
OL,13,Fcombination of higher taxes, rising
OL,14,Fwage costs, expensive energy and
OL,15,Ftighter financing conditions.
OL,17,FThe government should 'reconsider'
OL,18,Fsupport for businesses, Haldane told
OL,19,FITV News
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,FHigh energy costs were already a major
OL,8,Fdrag on the competitiveness of British
OL,9,Fmanufacturers before the war,
OL,10,Fparticularly for energy-intensive
OL,11,Findustries such as steel, chemicals
OL,12,Fand heavy industry.
OL,14,FLast year, the government said it
OL,15,Fwould cut electricity prices by up to
OL,16,F#40 per megawatt hour for 7,000 energy-
OL,17,Fintensive businesses by introducing
OL,18,Fthe British Industrial Competitiveness
OL,19,FScheme (BICS) in 2027.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,FHaldane believes the government should
OL,8,Fconsider acting sooner and being more
OL,9,Fgenerous.
OL,11,F"If there were a time to reconsider
OL,12,Fthe scale of that discount and the
OL,13,Ftiming - next year is a long way away
OL,14,F- that moment is now," he said.
OL,16,FAs the OECD forecasts demonstrate, the
OL,17,FUK's economic prospects have worsened
OL,18,Fsignificantly since the end of
OL,19,FFebruary.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,F"At the start of the year, I was
OL,8,Ftalking up the green shoots, which
OL,9,Fwere well-founded. Interest rates were
OL,10,Ffalling, people's pay packets were
OL,11,Fpicking up - those are the ingredients
OL,12,Ffor growth to take off. This is
OL,13,Fwithout question a setback," said
OL,14,FHaldane.
OL,16,FLiving standards are likely to come
OL,17,Funder pressure again, but he points
OL,18,Fout that wages are currently rising
OL,19,Ffaster than prices, offering some
OL,20,Freason for hope.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31112
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774605947
OL,3,CInterest rate cuts more likely than
OL,4,Chikes, says Bank's former chief
OL,5,Ceconomist
OL,7,F"Is it a setback that will crater
OL,8,Fgrowth? No, we are not yet at that
OL,9,Fpoint. Do we, though, need an
OL,10,Fuplifting, optimistic domestic
OL,11,Fnarrative to stir the animal spirits
OL,12,Fof business? Yes, we do. And that, I
OL,13,Fhope, will be forthcoming from
OL,14,Fgovernment in the months and weeks
OL,15,Fahead."
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
